# Cration des trimestres
import pandas as pd
pd.options.mode.chained_assignment = None  # default='warn'

evol_vente['trimestre'] = evol_vente['date'].dt.to_period('Q')
print(evol_vente.head())

# Chiffre d'affaire par trimestre pour les 3 annes
evol_vente_trim = evol_vente.groupby('trimestre')['price'].sum()
evol_vente_trim = evol_vente_trim.to_frame().reset_index()
print(evol_vente_trim.head())

# Trimestre 2021
evol_vente_2021 = evol_vente[(evol_vente['date'] > '2020-12-31') & (evol_vente['date'] <= '2021-12-31')]
print(evol_vente_2021.head())

# Trimestre 2022
evol_vente_2022 = evol_vente[(evol_vente['date'] > '2021-12-31') & (evol_vente['date'] <= '2022-12-31')]
print(evol_vente_2022.head())

# Trimestre 2023
evol_vente_2023 = evol_vente[(evol_vente['date'] > '2022-12-31') & (evol_vente['date'] <= '2023-12-31')]
print(evol_vente_2023.head())

# Visualisation du CA en fonction des trimestres
# Data
x = np.arange(9)
y = evol_vente_trim['price']
width = 0.2

plt.figure(figsize=[20, 9])

# Cration du diagramme
plt.bar(x, y, width)
plt.xticks(x, ["2021Q1", "2021Q2", "2021Q3", "2021Q4", "2022Q1", "2022Q2", "2022Q3", "2022Q4", "2023Q1"], fontsize=15)
plt.xlabel("Trimestre", fontsize=15)
plt.ylabel("Chiffre d'affaire", fontsize=15)
plt.legend(["Chiffre d'affaire"], fontsize=15)

# Courbe de Lorenz
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# 'Ct' Ajoutez une colonne numrique appele

# Dessin graphique

# Dessinez la distribution de frquence sur ax2

ax1.set_ylabel('pourcentages cumuls CA')

ax1.grid(True)

# Calcul coeff Gini
def gini_coefficient(x):
    """Compute Gini coefficient of array of values"""
    diffsum = 0
    for i, xi in enumerate(x[:-1], 1):
        diffsum += np.sum(np.abs(xi - x[i:]))
    return diffsum / (len(x)**2 * np.mean(x))

gini_coefficient(top_client['Ct'])

# Distribution des valeurs quantitatives
test = clients_amateurs.groupby(['client_id', 'age'])['price'].sum().reset_index()
third_quartile = test['price'].quantile(0.75)
first_quartile =  test['price'].quantile(0.25)
iqr =   third_quartile - first_quartile

mask = (test['price'] > third_quartile + 1.5 * iqr) | (test['price'] < first_quartile - 1.5 * iqr)

sns.scatterplot(x='age', y='price', data=test.loc[~mask])

#load necessary packages and functions
import scipy.stats as stats
import numpy as np

#Chi-squared test statistic, sample size, and minimum of rows and columns
X2, p, dof, ex = stats.chi2_contingency(genre_cat, correction=False)
print(p)
n = np.sum(genre_cat)
minDim = min(genre_cat.shape)-1

#calculate Cramer's V 
V = np.sqrt((X2/n) / minDim)

#display Cramer's V

ax = sns.boxplot(data=panier_session, x=x, y=y, order=order)

#Annotation

annot.configure(test='Kruskal', text_format='star', loc='outside', verbose=2)
annot.apply_test()

#load necessary packages and functions
import scipy.stats as stats
import numpy as np

#Chi-squared test statistic, sample size, and minimum of rows and columns
#H0 : pas de diffrence entre les frquences ou les proportions des groupes
#H1 : il existe une diffrence entre les frquences des groupes, diffrence qui ne serait pas due au hasard.

X2, p, dof, ex = stats.chi2_contingency(categ_age, correction=False)
print(p)
n = np.sum(categ_age)
minDim = min(categ_age.shape)-1

#calculate Cramer's V 
V = np.sqrt((X2/n) / minDim)

#display Cramer's V
print(V)
